				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/349489873/in/set-72157594465762783/&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2007/01/07/badge.jpg&quot; width=&quot;115&quot; height=&quot;86&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named badge.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/349489873/in/set-72157594465762783/&quot;&gt;I got a press pass&lt;/a&gt;, the straightforward way. Went to the convention center, found the press registration office. Filled out the form. Printed yesterday's Scripting News, gave it to them. Stood my ground when challenged. Got the badge. Lots of other bloggers were there, all of them got credentials. Not sure they knew what blogs are, but &quot;Internet&quot; was an acceptable form of publication. (Postscript to &lt;a href=&quot;http://weblogs.jupiterresearch.com/analysts/gartenberg/archives/2007/01/bloggers_at_ces.html&quot;&gt;Gartenberg&lt;/a&gt; about bloggers and press passes.)" created="Sun, 07 Jan 2007 21:29:25 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.engadget.com/2007/01/07/live-coverage-of-netgears-press-hoedown/&quot;&gt;Two&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.livedigitally.com/2007/01/07/netgear-knocks-it-out-of-the-park-at-ces/&quot;&gt;reports&lt;/a&gt; on Netgear's product announcements. Moving video content around a house is something I've been playing with for the last few months, and I gotta say I don't believe Netgear has a product that works for most people. You need a file server for sure, but every TV set must, imho, have its own hard disk and CPU. I prefer the Mac OS and I'd love to get a few Seagate TB disks. Such a setup does make the TV a lot more expensive (today) but I think it's the only solution that actually has a chance of working. Pretty likely Gates is going to talk about something like this tonight, and his solution almost certainly will put a hard disk and CPU at every TV (he sells OSes after all)." created="Sun, 07 Jan 2007 22:23:18 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I'm going to the Bill Gates keynote with &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/349680361/&quot;&gt;Jeremy Toeman&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/349680229/in/set-72157594465762783/&quot;&gt;Ron Hirson&lt;/a&gt;." created="Mon, 08 Jan 2007 00:03:54 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/349499754/in/photostream/&quot;&gt;Pictures&lt;/a&gt; of the press room at the convention center." created="Sun, 07 Jan 2007 21:44:22 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://blip.tv/file/127694&quot;&gt;Movie&lt;/a&gt;: The Las Vegas strip flies by." created="Sun, 07 Jan 2007 22:02:38 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://blip.tv/file/127686&quot;&gt;Movie&lt;/a&gt;: In a cab on the way to the convention center Steve Gillmor makes an admission. Steve got a press pass too. &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Sun, 07 Jan 2007 21:46:49 GMT" type="outline"/>
