				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://nakedjen.blogs.com/nakedjen/2007/01/if_you_want_to_.html&quot;&gt;Naked Jen&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;I am me.  Nakedjen.  Who protests just about anything and everything.&quot;" created="Sun, 07 Jan 2007 17:42:42 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2007/01/07/immerse.gif&quot; width=&quot;122&quot; height=&quot;80&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named immerse.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://weblogs.jupiterresearch.com/analysts/gartenberg/archives/2007/01/bloggers_at_ces.html&quot;&gt;Michael Gartenberg on bloggers at CES&lt;/a&gt;. I don't count as one of them, at least not yet. Count me as a gawker, eyes wide open, gears stripped, not knowing where to begin. Like Michael I'm in awe of Peter and the Engadget folk. How do they do it? Me, I'm mostly going to tag along. I have my camera and laptop. And my cold is threatening to come back. I'm going to wear a sweater and warm jacket today, no fashionable sports jackets for this guy. And yesterday Furrier asked me who Gartenberg is. I said you gotta know Michael." created="Sun, 07 Jan 2007 15:37:47 GMT" type="outline"/>
