				<outline text="OpenID" created="Sat, 06 Jan 2007 16:43:43 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I followed the instructions &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.intertwingly.net/blog/2007/01/03/OpenID-for-non-SuperUsers&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to create an OpenID for myself at MyOpenId, and added the magic bits that associate this weblog with that ID:" created="Sat, 06 Jan 2007 16:40:30 GMT"/>
					<outline text="&amp;lt;link rel=&quot;openid.server&quot; href=&quot;http://www.myopenid.com/server&quot; /&gt;"/>
					<outline text="&amp;lt;link rel=&quot;openid.delegate&quot; href=&quot;http://davew.myopenid.com/&quot; /&gt;"/>
					<outline text="If you do a View-Source you'll see these two link elements in the &amp;lt;head&gt; section of the HTML." created="Sat, 06 Jan 2007 16:45:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="So now I can use any of the services that use OpenID as an identity system, and not have to create a new identity. " created="Sat, 06 Jan 2007 16:44:08 GMT"/>
					<outline text="It took a few years, but it's great to see software actually being built around the identities that aren't vendor controlled. " created="Sat, 06 Jan 2007 16:46:24 GMT"/>
