				<outline text="Are you Under the Radar?" created="Fri, 05 Jan 2007 14:32:13 GMT" type="outline">
					<outline text="I am part of the selection committee for the next Under the Radar &lt;a href=&quot;http://undertheradarblog.com/2006/12/14/under-the-radar-call-for-companies/&quot;&gt;conference&lt;/a&gt;, on March 23 in Mountain View, CA. " created="Fri, 05 Jan 2007 14:32:17 GMT"/>
					<outline text="My main responsibility is to help them find interesting companies with products in relevant categories that aren't very well-known. " created="Fri, 05 Jan 2007 14:42:29 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The goal of the conference is to help draw attention to those products, and help get them staffed and funded, and successful. " created="Fri, 05 Jan 2007 14:42:12 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Naturally, I wanted to blog about this, so we could get the idea out in front of Scripting News readers. " created="Fri, 05 Jan 2007 14:37:16 GMT"/>
					<outline text="They're looking for companies with products in the following eight areas:" created="Fri, 05 Jan 2007 14:37:49 GMT"/>
					<outline text="1. Organize - Tasks, Database, Project, Notes, Bookmarks,"/>
					<outline text="2. Collaborate - Groups, Wikis, Spreadsheets, Word Processing, File Sending, Document Management"/>
					<outline text="3. Track - Time, Expenses, Budgets, Accounting, HR"/>
					<outline text="4. Publish - Blog platforms, Web publishing, Feeds/RSS, Content Management"/>
					<outline text="5. Communicate - Email, IM, VOIP, Voice, web conferencing"/>
					<outline text="6. Create - Presentation Mngr, music, photo edit/manage"/>
					<outline text="7. Personalize - Desktop, Calendar, personal organizers"/>
					<outline text="8. Search - vertical, social, create your own"/>
					<outline text="&lt;b&gt;How to proceed&lt;/b&gt;. If you know a company with a worthwhile product in any of these areas, one that isn't well-known, but has potential, please post a &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.wordpress.com/2007/01/05/scripting-news-for-152007/#comments&quot;&gt;comment here&lt;/a&gt;, with a pointer to their website, and I'll pass them on to the people running the conference. Should be pretty interesting! &quot;;-&gt;&quot;" created="Fri, 05 Jan 2007 14:39:12 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
